{"title_page": "Satya Priya Mahathero", "text_new": "{{short description|Bangladeshi Buddhist leader}}\n{{Infobox religious biography\n| name           = Satya Priya Mahathero\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| religion       = [[Buddhist]]\n| denomination   = \n| alias          = \n| location       = \n| Title          = \n| Period         = \n| Predecessor    = \n| Successor      = \n| ordination     = \n| post           = \n| previous_post  = \n| present_post   = \n| birth_name     = Bidhu Bhushan Barua\n| birth_date     = {{birth date|1930|06|10|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Cox's Bazar District|Cox's Bazar]], [[Bengal Presidency]], [[British India]]\n| death_date     = {{death date and age|2019|10|04|1930|06|10|df=y}}\n| death_place    = [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]]\n}}\n\n'''Satya Priya Mahathero''' (born '''Bidhu Bhiushan Barua''',<ref name=c/> 10 June 1930 \u2013 4 October 2019) was a [[Bangladeshi]] [[Buddhist]] pundit, religious leader and social worker. He was the President of Bangladesh Sangharaj Bhikkhu Mahasava.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.prothomalo.com/bangladesh/article/439795/\u09b0\u09be\u09ae\u09c1\u09b0-\u09b8\u09c0\u09ae\u09be-\u09ac\u09bf\u09b9\u09be\u09b0\u09c7-\u09ac\u09cc\u09a6\u09cd\u09a7-\u09ae\u09b9\u09be\u09b8\u09ae\u09cd\u09ae\u09c7\u09b2\u09a8|title=\u09b0\u09be\u09ae\u09c1\u09b0 \u09b8\u09c0\u09ae\u09be \u09ac\u09bf\u09b9\u09be\u09b0\u09c7 \u09ac\u09cc\u09a6\u09cd\u09a7 \u09ae\u09b9\u09be\u09b8\u09ae\u09cd\u09ae\u09c7\u09b2\u09a8|language=bn|date=1 February 2015|accessdate=4 October 2019|website=Prothom Alo\n}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nSatya Priya Mahathero was born on 10 June 1930 in South Merongloa Village of Fatekharpul Union which is situated in [[Ramu Upazila]] of [[Cox's Bazar District]].<ref name=a/> His father was Harakumar Barua and his mother was Premamayi Barua.<ref name=b/> \n\nMahathero received [[pravrajya]] in February 1950 from Binayacharya Aryabangsha Mahathero and dedicated himself to human beings.<ref name=a/> Six months later he became a [[bhikkhu]] on [[Maghi Purnima]].<ref name=b/> He received [[Ekushey Padak]] in 2015 for social service.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/15-named-for-ekushey-padak-63832\n|title=15 named for Ekushey Padak\n|date=8 February 2015|accessdate=4 October 2019|website=The Daily Star\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/uncategorized/2015/02/08/15-selected-for-ekushey-padak-2\n|title=15 selected for Ekushey Padak\n|date=8 February 2015|accessdate=4 October 2019|website=Dhaka Tribune\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.observerbd.com/2015/02/09/71564.php\n|title=15 named for Ekushey Padak\n|date=9 February 2015|accessdate=4 October 2019|website=The Daily Observer\n}}</ref> \n\n====== ==Death== ======\n\nMahathero died on 4 October 2019 at the age of 89 at [[Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University|Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University Hospital]], [[Dhaka]].<ref name=c>{{cite web|url=https://www.ekushey-tv.com/\u098f\u0995\u09c1\u09b6\u09c7-\u09aa\u09a6\u0995\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09aa\u09cd\u09a4-\u09aa\u09a8\u09cd\u09a1\u09bf\u09a4-\u09b8\u09a4\u09cd\u09af\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09bf\u09af\u09bc-\u09ae\u09b9\u09be\u09a5\u09c7\u09b0-\u0986\u09b0-\u09a8\u09c7\u0987/80887\n|title=\u098f\u0995\u09c1\u09b6\u09c7 \u09aa\u09a6\u0995\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09aa\u09cd\u09a4 \u09aa\u09a8\u09cd\u09a1\u09bf\u09a4 \u09b8\u09a4\u09cd\u09af\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09bf\u09af\u09bc \u09ae\u09b9\u09be\u09a5\u09c7\u09b0 \u0986\u09b0 \u09a8\u09c7\u0987\n|language=bn|date=4 October 2019|accessdate=4 October 2019|website=Ekushey Television\n}}</ref><ref name=a>{{cite web|url=https://www.jugantor.com/capital/228108/\u098f\u0995\u09c1\u09b6\u09c7-\u09aa\u09a6\u0995\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09aa\u09cd\u09a4-\u09aa\u09a8\u09cd\u09a1\u09bf\u09a4-\u09b8\u09a4\u09cd\u09af\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09bf\u09af\u09bc-\u09ae\u09b9\u09be\u09a5\u09c7\u09b0-\u0986\u09b0-\u09a8\u09c7\u0987\n|title=\u098f\u0995\u09c1\u09b6\u09c7 \u09aa\u09a6\u0995\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09aa\u09cd\u09a4 \u09aa\u09a8\u09cd\u09a1\u09bf\u09a4 \u09b8\u09a4\u09cd\u09af\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09bf\u09af\u09bc \u09ae\u09b9\u09be\u09a5\u09c7\u09b0 \u0986\u09b0 \u09a8\u09c7\u0987\n|language=bn|date=4 October 2019|accessdate=4 October 2019|website=Jugantor\n}}</ref><ref name=b>{{cite web|url=http://www.dainikamadershomoy.com/post/219987\n|title=\u098f\u0995\u09c1\u09b6\u09c7 \u09aa\u09a6\u0995\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09be\u09aa\u09cd\u09a4 \u09aa\u09a8\u09cd\u09a1\u09bf\u09a4 \u09b8\u09a4\u09cd\u09af\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09bf\u09af\u09bc \u09ae\u09b9\u09be\u09a5\u09c7\u09b0 \u09ae\u09be\u09b0\u09be \u0997\u09c7\u099b\u09c7\u09a8\n|language=bn|date=4 October 2019|accessdate=4 October 2019|website=Amader Shomoy\n}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mahathero, Satya Priya}}\n[[Category:1930 births]]\n[[Category:2019 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Cox's Bazar District]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Ekushey Padak]]\n[[Category:Buddhist religious leaders]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi Buddhists]]\n\n\n{{Bangladesh-reli-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Bangladeshi Buddhist leader}}\n{{Infobox religious biography\n| name           = Satya Priya Mahathero\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| religion       = [[Buddhist]]\n| denomination   = \n| alias          = \n| location       = \n| Title          = \n| Period         = \n| Predecessor    = \n| Successor      = \n| ordination     = \n| post           = \n| previous_post  = \n| present_post   = \n| birth_name     = Bidhu Bhushan Barua\n| birth_date     = {{birth date|1930|06|10|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Cox's Bazar District|Cox's Bazar]], [[Bengal Presidency]], [[British India]]\n| death_date     = {{death date and age|2019|10|04|1930|06|10|df=y}}\n| death_place    = [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]]\n}}\n\n'''Satya Priya Mahathero''' (born '''Bidhu Bhiushan Barua''',<ref name=c/> 10 June 1930 \u2013 4 October 2019) was a [[Bangladeshi]] [[Buddhist]] pundit, religious leader and social worker. He was the President of Bangladesh Sangharaj Bhikkhu Mahasava.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.prothomalo.com/bangladesh/article/439795/\u09b0\u09be\u09ae\u09c1\u09b0-\u09b8\u09c0\u09ae\u09be-\u09ac\u09bf\u09b9\u09be\u09b0\u09c7-\u09ac\u09cc\u09a6\u09cd\u09a7-\u09ae\u09b9\u09be\u09b8\u09ae\u09cd\u09ae\u09c7\u09b2\u09a8|title=\u09b0\u09be\u09ae\u09c1\u09b0 \u09b8\u09c0\u09ae\u09be \u09ac\u09bf\u09b9\u09be\u09b0\u09c7 \u09ac\u09cc\u09a6\u09cd\u09a7 \u09ae\u09b9\u09be\u09b8\u09ae\u09cd\u09ae\u09c7\u09b2\u09a8|language=bn|date=1 February 2015|accessdate=4 October 2019|website=Prothom Alo\n}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nSatya Priya Mahathero was born on 10 June 1930 in South Merongloa Village of Fatekharpul Union which is situated in [[Ramu Upazila]] of [[Cox's Bazar District]].<ref name=a/> His father was Harakumar Barua and his mother was Premamayi Barua.<ref name=b/> \n\nMahathero received [[pravrajya]] in February 1950 from Binayacharya Aryabangsha Mahathero and dedicated himself to human beings.<ref name=a/> Six months later he became a [[bhikkhu]] on [[Maghi Purnima]].<ref name=b/> He received [[Ekushey Padak]] in 2015 for social service.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/15-named-for-ekushey-padak-63832\n|title=15 named for Ekushey Padak\n|date=8 February 2015|accessdate=4 October 2019|website=The Daily Star\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/uncategorized/2015/02/08/15-selected-for-ekushey-padak-2\n|title=15 selected for Ekushey Padak\n|date=8 February 2015|accessdate=4 October 2019|website=Dhaka Tribune\n}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.observerbd.com/2015/02/09/71564.php\n|title=15 named for Ekushey Padak\n|date=9 February 2015|accessdate=4 October 2019|website=The Daily Observer\n}}</ref>\n\nMahathero died on 4 October 2019 at the age of 89 at [[Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University|Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University Hospital]], [[Dhaka]].<ref name=c>{{cite web|url=https:/